Avoid asserting on stale BG state after the BG instance was already destroyed.

WorldSession::HandleMoveWorldportAckOpcode already detects the case where
the player's destination is a battleground map whose instance no longer
exists, and tries to recover via the local returnHomeFunc lambda. That
lambda calls sMapMgr.CreateMap(loc.mapid, player) which, for a BG map id,
dispatches to MapManager::CreateInstance — and the first thing
CreateInstance does for a BG entry is:

    NewInstanceId = player->GetBattleGroundId();
    MANGOS_ASSERT(NewInstanceId);

If the player was already removed from the BG between sending the
Worldport ACK and the server processing it (a common race when bots
cycle in and out of queues at scale), GetBattleGroundId() is 0 and the
assert aborts the worldserver. The crash log emits literally

    Critical Error: A condition which must never be false was found to be false ...
    CreateInstance(): NewInstanceId

(__FUNCTION__ : STRINGIZE(CONDITION) from the WPError macro), followed
by SIGABRT and a core dump. Incident: homelab cmangos-classic, repeating
roughly every 6-7h on a BG-bot-heavy load, May 2026.

The recovery is the same shape the function already uses one branch up
when MapManager::IsValidMapCoord fails: drop the stale BG state, clear
the teleport-far semaphore, and reissue the teleport to homebind. This
side-steps returnHomeFunc entirely for the "BG vanished" case so no one
calls CreateInstance on a map id that can't legally have an instance
for this player anymore.

--- a/src/game/MotionGenerators/MovementHandler.cpp
+++ b/src/game/MotionGenerators/MovementHandler.cpp
@@ -106,10 +106,17 @@
         if (!map)
         {
-            DETAIL_LOG("WorldSession::HandleMoveWorldportAckOpcode: %s was teleported far to nonexisten battleground instance "
-                       " (map:%u, x:%f, y:%f, z:%f) Trying to port him to his previous place..",
-                       GetPlayer()->GetGuidStr().c_str(), loc.mapid, loc.coord_x, loc.coord_y, loc.coord_z);
-
-            returnHomeFunc();
+            // returnHomeFunc would call sMapMgr.CreateMap on a BG map id;
+            // MapManager::CreateInstance then asserts MANGOS_ASSERT(NewInstanceId)
+            // when the player's BG was already cleared by RemovePlayer —
+            // exactly the abort observed in our homelab (CreateInstance():
+            // NewInstanceId, SIGABRT). Recover the way the IsValidMapCoord
+            // branch above does: drop stale BG state and teleport home.
+            sLog.outError("WorldSession::HandleMoveWorldportAckOpcode: %s teleported far to nonexistent BG instance "
+                          "(map:%u, x:%f, y:%f, z:%f); clearing BG state, sending to homebind.",
+                          GetPlayer()->GetGuidStr().c_str(), loc.mapid, loc.coord_x, loc.coord_y, loc.coord_z);
+            GetPlayer()->SetBattleGroundId(0, BATTLEGROUND_TYPE_NONE);
+            GetPlayer()->SetSemaphoreTeleportFar(false);
+            GetPlayer()->TeleportToHomebind();
             return;
         }
     }
